Join the Formerly Incarcerated, Convicted People and Families Movement (FICPFM) for its 2026 Regional Convenings, where organizers, advocates, and community leaders from across the country will gather to strengthen relationships, share strategies, and build collective power. These regional gatherings create opportunities to collaborate with people closest to the work happening in your own community while celebrating 15 years of movement building and leadership. Attendees will have the chance to connect with organizations working across a range of justice issues, build new partnerships, and deepen their impact. Be sure to grab Plan C materials, abortion pills by mail resources, and free mini swag while you're there.
